issue.title: External links should use the external link icons, by default
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
When viewing a MD text hyperlink, users have no way to know if the link will open an external browser window or not.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
The **open in new** icon should be added to links that open a new window (that is, that link to something outside of the current domain).

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
The image/icon could manually be added to every link, but that (1) becomes a maintenance nightmare and (2) makes it impossible to change out iconsets.

**Additional context**
Would be nice to be able to:
1. Define the exact icon to use (e.g., **https://fonts.google.com/icons?icon.query=open+in+new**)
2. Define the exact "home" domain.
3. Be able to also add (or not) the icon on-demand.

issue.body:
Bumps [@cypress/request](https://github.com/cypress-io/request) to 3.0.1 and updates ancestor dependency [cypress](https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress). These dependencies need to be updated together. Updates `@cypress/request` from 2.88.12 to 3.0.1

Sourced from @​cypress/request's releases.

3.0.1 (2023-09-06)

Bug Fixes

v3.0.0

3.0.0 (2023-08-08)

Features

  • Add allowInsecureRedirect option (c5bcf21)

BREAKING CHANGES

  • The allowInsecureRedirect is false by default, which may cause issues if your usage relies on insecure redirects. For the former behavior, you can opt in to insecure redirects by setting the option to true, but it is not recommended.

Co-authored-by: Szymon Drosdzol szymon@doyensec.com
